{"version":1,"ops":[{"type":3,"author":{"id":"e6c152d440109efdc7afc4e9ac4ac193043f8f68"},"timestamp":1510758128,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM0NDYxOTIzNg==","github-url":"https://github.com/letoram/arcan/issues/129#issuecomment-344619236"},"message":"You can cmake with -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Debug for much more verbose logging, but this smells like a DRM_MASTER issue. Short story, there's a hidden root-only capability required to use the card node and it relates to how display managers, display servers and so on are supposed to negotiate display access - I'm guessing something else on your system holds this capability.\n\nThere's an ugly protocol for dealing with this (which may or may not involve distribution specific stuff like logind, proxy-suid launchers), - I've avoided implementing support for that pending a refactor of the gpu- configuration code.\n\nTwo options, if no-one has tried to use the card0 already (so boot into console and run without Xorg on a VT), the first user with device permissions will get a pseudo-\"drmMaster\" capability without being root. The other is well, icky, i.e. being root.\n\nProtip (and I should really update the welcome appl): use ../tests/interactive/eventtest instead for testing when running from the console, as it has a safety shutdown timeout if no keyboard is detected or present.","files":null},{"type":3,"author":{"id":"0e4676a3878b12da05d083d12f4d1b557361dcdc"},"timestamp":1510759592,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM0NDYyNzE1NQ==","github-url":"https://github.com/letoram/arcan/issues/129#issuecomment-344627155"},"message":"Tried rebooting and running Arcan before anything else (except the VT and Zsh, obviously), and tried running with sudo. Neither noticeably affected the output.","files":null},{"type":3,"author":{"id":"e6c152d440109efdc7afc4e9ac4ac193043f8f68"},"timestamp":1510761980,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM0NDY0MDQ3Mw==","github-url":"https://github.com/letoram/arcan/issues/129#issuecomment-344640473"},"message":"interesting, that should rule drm-master out, - the \"i965_dri.so does not support the 0xffffffff PCI ID.\" message hint that this might be further down in the graphics stack (mesa, libdrm, driver).\n\n1. does weston (wayland reference compositor) display the same error?\n2. more data: kernel \u0026 libdrm version + output from debug build of arcan with LIBGL_DEBUG=verbose environment and if there's anything in dmesg.","files":null},{"type":3,"author":{"id":"0e4676a3878b12da05d083d12f4d1b557361dcdc"},"timestamp":1510762602,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM0NDY0Mzg1NA==","github-url":"https://github.com/letoram/arcan/issues/129#issuecomment-344643854"},"message":"Weston works fine. (Well, it starts. The terminal just fades away immediately, so it's completely unusable.)\n\n`uname -a` is `Linux Lorence 4.13.12-1-ARCH #1 SMP PREEMPT Wed Nov 8 11:54:06 CET 2017 x86_64 GNU/Linux`\n\n`libdrm` is version `2.4.88-1` according to pacman\n\n`LIBGL_DEBUG=verbose` adds an extra line `libGL: Can't open configuration file /home/yuki/.drirc: No such file or directory.` just before the `failed to initialize EGL`, but otherwise no difference. (Used as an environment variable. If it was supposed to be a compilation flag, my mistake.)","files":null},{"type":3,"author":{"id":"0e4676a3878b12da05d083d12f4d1b557361dcdc"},"timestamp":1510762923,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM0NDY0NTY0NQ==","github-url":"https://github.com/letoram/arcan/issues/129#issuecomment-344645645"},"message":"Oh, and mesa is version `17.2.5-1`,  and `dmesg` says nothing.","files":null},{"type":3,"author":{"id":"e6c152d440109efdc7afc4e9ac4ac193043f8f68"},"timestamp":1510763854,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM0NDY1MDg5OQ==","github-url":"https://github.com/letoram/arcan/issues/129#issuecomment-344650899"},"message":"the LIBGL_ was indeed an environmental variable - but versions etc. all seems reasonable. Ok so this is narrowed down to the EGL setup itself, (unless weston actually switched to its kms-fb backend, but I don't remember how that part works).\n\nThere's another environment variable that should get us closer,  EGL_LOG_LEVEL=debug","files":null},{"type":3,"author":{"id":"0e4676a3878b12da05d083d12f4d1b557361dcdc"},"timestamp":1510764205,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM0NDY1MjgxNg==","github-url":"https://github.com/letoram/arcan/issues/129#issuecomment-344652816"},"message":"Here's with `EGL_LOG_LEVEL=debug`: [arcan.log](https://github.com/letoram/arcan/files/1475522/arcan.log). It mentions something about x11, not sure if that's relevant.","files":null},{"type":3,"author":{"id":"e6c152d440109efdc7afc4e9ac4ac193043f8f68"},"timestamp":1510764753,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM0NDY1NTcwNA==","github-url":"https://github.com/letoram/arcan/issues/129#issuecomment-344655704"},"message":"it's relevant, and likely the reason, i.e. it couldn't derive the EGL platform from the display handle I provide. There's an extension I can use to get around that, adding to the work-queue, but you should be able to test/ override this with the environment:\nEGL_PLATFORM=drm","files":null},{"type":3,"author":{"id":"0e4676a3878b12da05d083d12f4d1b557361dcdc"},"timestamp":1510765118,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM0NDY1NzYwNA==","github-url":"https://github.com/letoram/arcan/issues/129#issuecomment-344657604"},"message":"[arcan.log](https://github.com/letoram/arcan/files/1475585/arcan.log)\n\nDoesn't seem to change anything.","files":null},{"type":3,"author":{"id":"e6c152d440109efdc7afc4e9ac4ac193043f8f68"},"timestamp":1510766233,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM0NDY2MzMwMQ==","github-url":"https://github.com/letoram/arcan/issues/129#issuecomment-344663301"},"message":"I'll try implement the extension, bbiab.","files":null},{"type":3,"author":{"id":"e6c152d440109efdc7afc4e9ac4ac193043f8f68"},"timestamp":1510771014,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDE